### Phase E — API Gateway

---

**`services/api-gateway/Dockerfile`**

```dockerfile
FROM kong:3.6

USER root
COPY kong.yml /etc/kong/kong.yml
USER kong
```

This is minimal — Kong reads `kong.yml` at startup via the `KONG_DECLARATIVE_CONFIG` env var set in `docker-compose.yml`.

---

**`services/api-gateway/kong.yml`**

```yaml
_format_version: "3.0"
_transform: true

services:
  - name: auth-service
    url: http://auth-service:3001
    routes:
      - name: auth-routes
        paths:
          - /api/auth
        strip_path: false
        protocols: [http, https]

  - name: territory-service
    url: http://territory-service:3002
    routes:
      - name: territory-routes
        paths:
          - /api/territory
        strip_path: false
        protocols: [http, https]

  - name: vote-service
    url: http://vote-service:3003
    routes:
      - name: vote-routes
        paths:
          - /api/vote
        strip_path: false
        protocols: [http, https]
      - name: vote-ws-route
        paths:
          - /ws/vote
        strip_path: false
        protocols: [ws, wss]

  - name: economy-service
    url: http://economy-service:3004
    routes:
      - name: economy-routes
        paths:
          - /api/economy
        strip_path: false
        protocols: [http, https]

  - name: profile-service
    url: http://profile-service:3005
    routes:
      - name: profile-routes
        paths:
          - /api/profile
        strip_path: false
        protocols: [http, https]

plugins:
  - name: jwt
    config:
      secret_is_base64: false
      claims_to_verify:
        - exp
    route: null  # applies globally; restrict per-route once routes are stable

  - name: rate-limiting
    config:
      minute: 120
      hour: 3000
      policy: local
      fault_tolerant: true
      hide_client_headers: false

  - name: cors
    config:
      origins:
        - "http://localhost:5173"  # Vite dev server
        - "https://feastfite.com"
      methods:
        - GET
        - POST
        - PUT
        - PATCH
        - DELETE
        - OPTIONS
      headers:
        - Accept
        - Authorization
        - Content-Type
      credentials: true
      max_age: 3600
```

Kong 3.x declarative format gotchas:
1. `_format_version: "3.0"` is required — do not use `"2.1"`.
2. `_transform: true` allows Kong to apply default transformations (recommended).
3. The JWT plugin in DB-less mode requires consumers with JWT credentials to be defined in `kong.yml` as well. During the scaffolding phase, set the plugin at the global level with `enabled: false` or scope it only to authenticated routes — otherwise every request to `/health` will fail.
4. The WebSocket route (`/ws/vote`) must list `protocols: [ws, wss]` explicitly. Kong proxies WebSocket connections transparently once this is set.
5. Rate-limiting with `policy: local` is fine for single-instance Kong; switch to `policy: redis` in production with a shared Redis.

