`moduleResolution: "bundler"` is Vite's recommended setting — it resolves paths like Vite/esbuild does, supporting bare specifiers without `.js` extension. Note the `paths` here use `../` (one level up) because the frontend is at `frontend/` not `services/<name>/`.

