## Part 4 — Developer Parallelism Strategy

Once Phase A and Phase B are complete (root + shared package), 4 developers can work in parallel:

| Dev | Work Package |
|-----|-------------|
| Dev 1 | `services/auth-service` — full implementation (JWT issuance, pg schema, Redis sessions) |
| Dev 2 | `services/territory-service` — PostGIS queries, territory claim logic, event publishing |
| Dev 3 | `services/vote-service` + `services/economy-service` — vote session state machine, points ledger |
| Dev 4 | `frontend` — React components, routing, API client integration |

Profile-service can be picked up by any dev who finishes early, as it has no cross-service dependencies at the stub phase.

**Conflict zones to communicate about:**
- `packages/shared/src/types/index.ts` — all devs will want to add fields. Establish that type additions are append-only (no breaking changes to existing interfaces) and require a short Slack thread before merging.
- `docker-compose.yml` — only infra changes; agree that service additions are the only permitted changes during parallel dev phase.
- `services/api-gateway/kong.yml` — route additions only; no changes to existing plugin config.

