## Part 6 — Common Gotchas Reference

| Gotcha | Problem | Fix |
|--------|---------|-----|
| `@feastfite/shared` not found at runtime | `dist/` not built before Docker build | Always run `npm run build -w packages/shared` in CI before building service images |
| `ECONNREFUSED` on RabbitMQ at service startup | Race condition: service starts before RabbitMQ is ready | The `amqp.ts` reconnect loop handles this — just set `depends_on: rabbitmq: condition: service_healthy` |
| Kong returns 401 on `/health` | Global JWT plugin enabled | Disable JWT plugin globally; apply it only to authenticated routes via `route:` scoping in `kong.yml` |
| PostGIS `CREATE EXTENSION` fails | Extension not pre-loaded | `postgis/postgis:16-3.4` auto-creates it, but only for the default DB. Run `CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS postgis;` in migration scripts for `territory_db` |
| Windows bind mount permission errors | Docker Desktop + Windows NTFS | Use named volumes (already done in `docker-compose.yml`) instead of `./data:/var/lib/postgresql/data` bind mounts |
| npm workspace install installs wrong version | Running `npm install` in a service subdirectory | Always run `npm install` from the repo root. Per-subdirectory installs bypass hoisting |
| Vite HMR breaks behind Kong proxy | WebSocket HMR traffic not proxied | Vite dev server runs on 5173 directly; only API calls proxy through Kong. Do not proxy `localhost:5173` through Kong |
| `tsx watch` fails on Windows | Path separators in globs | Use `tsx watch src/index.ts` (explicit path, not glob) — already specified in all service `dev` scripts |
| Kong `_format_version: "2.1"` warning | Deprecated format in Kong 3.x | Use `"3.0"` — already specified in the plan |
| `docker-compose up` hangs on PostGIS | `postgis/postgis:16-3.4` initializes extensions on first start, slow | The healthcheck uses `pg_isready` which returns true before extension init completes. Add a 5-second `start_period` to the PostGIS healthcheck |

